text_section_content.markdown_text: Frequently Asked Questions

**Can a regular Costco member shop at the Costco Business Center?**
Yes! All Costco members can shop on CostcoBusinessDelivery.com or at any of the Costco Business Center warehouse locations.

**Do I need to purchase a special membership card to shop at the Costco Business Center?**
No. You can use your existing Costco membership card.

**Can I have items from the Costco Business Center delivered to my residential home address?**
No. All Costco members can get delivery for Items purchased on CostcoBusinessDelivery.com, but not to a residential address.

**How is CostcoBusinessDelivery.com different from Costco.com?**
CostcoBusinessDelivery.com does not have many of the standard items found on Costco.com, like jewelry, clothing, and hearing aids, but it does have a great mix of must-have items for all Costco members, as well as a large selection of essential business items. You'll find appliances, catering items, individually wrapped snacks, and an expanded selection of soft drinks and other beverages. Plus, our food and grocery items are available in bulk quantities, making it easy for you to stock up on your favorite products. CostcoBusinessDelivery.com also holds impressive Savings Events where you can find amazing deals on a wide variety of items. And just like Costco.com, there's no coupon clipping required–savings are conveniently applied at check-out.

text_section_content.markdown_text: Save Money with High Volume Purchases

Many of the products sold at the Costco Business Center are available for purchase by the pallet or truckload. Take advantage of competitive pricing and possible savings on freight to maximize your bottom line. There are many households and businesses that use particular products on a daily basis, which they simply can't afford to be without. Whether it's insulated cups and stir sticks for your coffee stand, or laundry soap for your growing family, purchasing products by the pallet or truckload offers a great opportunity to substantially stock up on items you know you will need. Imagine the convenience and peace of mind, knowing you have enough supplies to last you 6 months or even a year!

At CostcoBusinessDelivery.com, we make ordering simple and easy. We have experienced marketing representatives that work with you in person, on the phone or via email, to build a pallet or truckload tailored to your specific needs.
We can build a truckload 3 different ways:

1. With 1 item
2. With 2 or more items from the same supplier whose distribution point is the same for all items
3. With full pallets of multiple items from your local Costco Business Center
[Learn more about Domestic or Export Volume Sales](https://www.costcobusinessdelivery.com/truckload.html)
